subSubSection.paragraph:
(
Figs 3–17
)

Pronotum with well-developed apical and basal lobes, deep anterior and posterior grooves and a smooth virtually globular disc (
Figs 3
, 
5
), anterior margin of apical lobe and posterior margin of basal lobe narrowly bordered (
Fig. 4
). Right metepisternum and metepimeron, as well as visible portions of abdominal sternites without setae; metepisternum approximately 2.8 times longer than wide (
Fig. 14
).

